
<p>Juli Clover, MacRumors:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Apple today provided developers with the fourth betas of <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/ios-26/">iOS
26</a> and <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/ipados-26/">iPadOS 26</a> for testing purposes, with the
updates coming two weeks after Apple <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/07/07/apple-seeds-ios-26-beta-3/">seeded the third
betas</a>.</p>
</blockquote>

<p><a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/07/22/apple-seeds-macos-tahoe-beta-4/">MacOS</a>, <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/07/22/apple-seeds-watchos-26-beta-4/">WatchOS, tvOS, and VisionOS</a> too, all in lockstep. Also, a <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/07/22/ios-26-beta-4-features/">good first look at what’s changed in iOS 26 beta 4 from beta 3</a>. Some of the things Apple is tweaking between betas <a href="https://mastodon.social/@gruber/114899907908341231">need more than minor tweaking</a>. Also: Apple Intelligence summaries for news notifications <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/07/22/ios-26-beta-4-notification-summaries/">are back</a>.</p>

